INSERT INTO public.questions (exam_id, subject_id, topic_id, year, paper, question_text, option_1, option_2, option_3, option_4, correct_option, explanation, difficulty) VALUES
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct in the context of a capitalist society? I. Only those consumer goods are produced that are in demand. II. The goods produced are distributed among people on the basis of Purchasing Power.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: capitalism produces goods based on demand, and distribution is based on purchasing power (ability to pay).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Government bonds are issued with original maturity of ______.', 'less than 120 days', '90 days or more', 'one year or more', 'less than one year', 3, 'Government bonds are long-term debt instruments with original maturity of one year or more (up to 30 years or more).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Price elasticity of demand for a good can be expressed as ______.', 'percentage change in income / percentage change in price', 'net change in price / percentage change in demand', 'percentage change in demand / percentage change in price', 'net change in quantity / percentage change in supply', 3, 'Price elasticity of demand = (% change in quantity demanded) / (% change in price).', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The speculative demand for money can be written as (where r is the market rate of interest and rmax and rmin are the upper and lower limits of r)', '(rmax + r)/(r - rmin)', '(rmax - r)/(r - rmin)', '(rmax - r)/(r + rmin)', '(rmax + r)/(r + rmin)', 2, 'Speculative demand for money = (rmax - r)/(r - rmin), representing the Keynesian liquidity preference theory.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The concept of human development was introduced by ______.', 'Amartya Sen', 'Mahbub ul Haq', 'Jean Drèze', 'Martha Nussbaum', 2, 'Mahbub ul Haq introduced the concept of Human Development (UNDP) and the Human Development Index, drawing on Amartya Sen''s work on capabilities.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'e587b482-1005-40dc-b6dd-3d9c2119a753'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The National Highways constitute about ______ percent of the total road length in India?', '2', '4', '12', '18', 1, 'National Highways constitute about 2% of the total road length in India but carry about 40% of the traffic.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '3e74357f-d7ad-4652-8435-eaa0f7cdfef6'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development (NABARD)? I. NABARD was set up in 1972. II. NABARD was set up as an apex body to coordinate the activities of all institutions involved in the rural financing system.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 2, 'NABARD was set up in 1982 (not 1972). It is an apex body for rural financing coordination. So Only II is correct.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'As of July 2023, there are ________ districts in Telangana.', '28', '33', '36', '39', 2, 'As of July 2023, Telangana has 33 districts after the recent reorganization of districts in 2016 and further additions.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Annual Normal Rainfall in Telangana is ________ millimetres (mm).', '805.4', '875.4', '905.4', '975.4', 3, 'The annual normal rainfall in Telangana is approximately 905.4 mm, received mostly during the southwest monsoon.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Telangana is endowed with a rich diversity of flora and fauna with _____ mammal species.', '21', '28', '103', '365', 2, 'Telangana has about 28 mammal species as per various biodiversity assessments.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following pairs of ''wildlife sanctuary – district'' is/are correctly matched? I. Manjira Wild Life Sanctuary - Sangareddy II. Kinnerasani Wild Life Sanctuary - Medak', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 1, 'Manjira Wildlife Sanctuary is in Sangareddy district (correct). Kinnerasani Wildlife Sanctuary is in Khammam district, not Medak. So Only I is correct.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding Telangana state statistics as per Census 2011? I. Total number of Municipal Corporations is 129. II. Total number of Gram Panchayats is 12769.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 2, 'As per Census 2011, Telangana has 12769 Gram Panchayats (Statement II correct). The number of Municipal Corporations is less than 129. So Only II is correct.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'As per Census 2011, rural population of Telangana is _____ percent of the total population of the state.', '38.88', '36.12', '61.12', '63.88', 1, 'As per Census 2011, Telangana''s rural population was 38.88% of the total population.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding Telangana state statistics as per Census 2011? I. Total number of inhabited villages is 9834. II. Total number of un-inhabited villages is 379.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: Telangana has 9834 inhabited villages and 379 uninhabited villages as per Census 2011.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Telangana registered ______ percent growth rate in production of Foodgrains between 2019-20 and 2020-21.', '8.6', '14.6', '19.6', '22.6', 3, 'Telangana registered 19.6% growth in foodgrains production between 2019-20 and 2020-21, according to government data.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '63f54208-07b4-4014-b501-f8691de5e2c1'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'In the Export Preparedness Index 2021, Telangana has scored ______ in the Business environment indicator.', '85', '90', '95', '100', 2, 'Telangana scored 90 in the Business environment indicator of the Export Preparedness Index 2021.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'fece8020-1cd0-4cd3-ab7d-23d1da0243f9'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding the Road Transportation network in Telangana? I. 61.80 percent of the total road length in Telangana are rural roads. II. 9.56 percent of the total road length in Telangana are National Highways.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 1, '61.80% of Telangana''s road length is rural roads (Statement I correct). National Highways constitute only about 2.8% (not 9.56%). So Only I is correct.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Raja Rajeswara (Rajanna) Temple is situated in ______ town of Telangana.', 'Vemulawada', 'Alampur', 'Bhadrachalam', 'Basara', 1, 'Raja Rajeswara (Rajanna) Temple is located in Vemulawada, Karimnagar district, dedicated to Lord Shiva.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Bathukamma is a festival of _____. This festival is treated as a symbol of Telangana''s cultural identity.', 'bulls', 'flowers', 'trumpets', 'elephants', 2, 'Bathukamma is a floral festival celebrated in Telangana, where women arrange flowers in a conical shape and worship the goddess Gauri.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'The narratives of which of the following art forms describe struggles against exploitation?', 'Golla Suddulu', 'Oggu Kathalu', 'Gotralu', 'Dhoom Dham', 2, 'Oggu Kathalu are folk narratives that describe struggles against exploitation, performed by the Oggu community in Telangana.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct in the context of the State symbols of Telangana? I. Tangedu flower is used during the Batukamma festival by women folk. II. Lord Rama worshipped Jammi Chettu before invading Lanka and vanquished Ravana.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: Tangedu flowers are used in Bathukamma, and Lord Rama worshipped Jammi Chettu (Prosopis cineraria) before the Lanka invasion.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding the Banjara Needle Crafts? I. Banjara Needle Crafts are the traditional handmade fabrics made by Banjaras (the tribal Gypsies) in Telangana. II. It is a form of embroidery and mirror work on fabrics employing the needlecraft.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: Banjara needle crafts are traditional handmade fabrics by Banjaras, involving embroidery and mirror work.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, 'c14a6349-1631-4eb0-8302-f2c798195166'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding Medak Cathedral? I. It was built by Charles Walker Fasnet. II. It was consecrated on 25 December 1904.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: Medak Cathedral was built by Charles Walker Fasnet and consecrated on December 25, 1904.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '63f54208-07b4-4014-b501-f8691de5e2c1'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding the Mana Ooru-Mana Badi Programme? I. Telangana State Government started the programme for comprehensive development and strengthening of Infrastructure facilities in 26,065 Schools in 3 phases spread over 3 years. II. The programme was started with total budget outlay of Rs.17289 crores.', 'Only I', 'Only II', 'Both I and II', 'Neither I nor II', 3, 'Both statements are correct: the programme covers 26,065 schools over 3 phases with a total budget of ₹17,289 crores.', 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668'::uuid, 'aa8d32e0-c642-49ea-934c-af0f7fd9986a'::uuid, '385bbfda-8fa8-4d58-98a8-7b26d3a3c13b'::uuid, 2023, 'Paper-I', 'On 17 September 1948, the Indian government conducted a military operation called ______ to bring Hyderabad state into the Indian Union.', 'Operation Trident', 'Operation Vijay', 'Operation Python', 'Operation Polo', 4, 'Operation Polo was the police action conducted by the Indian government on 17 September 1948 to annex Hyderabad into the Indian Union.', 'medium')
